abstract: Because she rented the billboards, Kat Sullivan may face more than $40,000 in fines for not registering as a lobbyist.
snippet: Because she rented the billboards, Kat Sullivan may face more than $40,000 in fines for not registering as a lobbyist.
lead_paragraph: When Kat Sullivan rented a billboard last year in upstate New York to call for stronger protections against child sex abusers, she believed she was engaging in the democratic process, using her own time and money to make her voice as an abuse survivor heard.

abstract: Quentin Tarantino’s film is filled with references to TV shows, movies and other totems of midcentury Los Angeles. We explain who’s who and what’s what.
snippet: Quentin Tarantino’s film is filled with references to TV shows, movies and other totems of midcentury Los Angeles. We explain who’s who and what’s what.
lead_paragraph: It’s no coincidence that the title “Once Upon a Time … in Hollywood” evokes, as A.O. Scott pointed out in his New York Times review, “bedtime stories as well as a pair of Sergio Leone masterpieces.”

abstract: Out on Pier 17 in the seaport district, Jean-Georges Vongerichten has opened a seafood restaurant called the Fulton.
snippet: Out on Pier 17 in the seaport district, Jean-Georges Vongerichten has opened a seafood restaurant called the Fulton.
lead_paragraph: Sooner or later, those of us who follow the career of Jean-Georges Vongerichten reach a point where our memories can’t keep up. The tuna tartares start to run together; we can’t recall whether it’s served in lettuce cups with threads of shiso at Perry St. or at JoJo. At some point it’s hard to recall what makes the chicken breast inside a resoundingly crunchy Parmesan crust at Nougatine different from the Parmesan-crusted chicken at the Mark.

abstract: In a key swing state, Democrats looking at the presidential field were more likely to follow their head than their heart in whom to support.
snippet: In a key swing state, Democrats looking at the presidential field were more likely to follow their head than their heart in whom to support.
lead_paragraph: NEWTOWN, Pa. — Diane LeBas, a 71-year-old substitute teacher attending the Newtown Democrats’ summer picnic on Sunday, recounted how she was tear-gassed protesting the Vietnam War. No one could question her progressivism.

abstract: For half of the candidates, it may be their last chance to make an impression on the national debate stage.
snippet: For half of the candidates, it may be their last chance to make an impression on the national debate stage.
lead_paragraph: When 20 Democratic presidential candidates gather for the second round of debates this Tuesday and Wednesday, about half of them will do so with the understanding that it will probably be their last time debating on the national stage this election cycle.

abstract: An early-season hangover seems to have subsided, but still the joy ride of 2018 obscures how good these Red Sox can be.
snippet: An early-season hangover seems to have subsided, but still the joy ride of 2018 obscures how good these Red Sox can be.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — The reminders hang over every member of the Boston Red Sox. At the top of each locker in the home clubhouse at Fenway Park is a nameplate with a logo commemorating the 2018 World Series title. It was the achievement of a lifetime for these Red Sox, and they still cannot quite fathom how it happened with such ease.
